title: Output parameter should display in data set dialog
description: When calling the stored procedure from the Oracle database, the query result has been stored in an output parameter as an object. However, while in the query result page, there is no data returned. The expected result is for the output parameter to display in the edit data set dialog.
OB: While in the query result page, there is no data returned.
EB: The output parameter should display in the data set dialog.
SR:
1. Call the stored procedure from the Oracle database.
2. Navigate to the query result page.
3. Observe that there is no data returned.
4. Verify that the output parameter is not displayed in the data set dialog.
